audience has to say

12:57.477 --> 12:59.144
after the Q&A, right?

12:59.146 --> 13:00.111
Who cares what they say?

13:00.113 --> 13:01.146
You made your first movie.

13:01.148 --> 13:03.548
I'm very proud of you.

13:03.550 --> 13:04.382
Proud.

13:04.384 --> 13:05.450
Of course.

13:06.820 --> 13:08.486
How was the premiere
in New York?

13:09.322 --> 13:10.421
It was good.

13:10.423 --> 13:12.357
Mostly positive reviews.

13:12.359 --> 13:13.959
A few negatives ones.

13:13.960 --> 13:15.560
Try not to pay as much
attention to those.

13:15.562 --> 13:17.462
Any publicity's good publicity.

13:19.166 --> 13:20.331
I guess so.

13:21.802 --> 13:23.067
Story looked familiar.

13:25.305 --> 13:27.305
Yeah, well, write what you know.

13:27.307 --> 13:28.973
Isn't that what they taught us?

13:28.975 --> 13:31.109
And you know this story?

13:31.111 --> 13:32.177
This is, uh.

13:32.179 --> 13:33.278
Crazy, I know.

13:34.514 --> 13:36.181
What's it
been, like six years?

13:36.183 --> 13:37.081
Five.

13:37.984 --> 13:39.551
Five years, uh huh.

13:41.488 --> 13:44.055
Is that you, is that really you?

13:45.091 --> 13:46.608
I have so many questions.

13:46.609 --> 13:48.126
I don't even know if I
want the answers anymore.

13:48.128 --> 13:49.027
I do.

13:49.863 --> 13:51.129
Tell me everything.

13:51.131 --> 13:52.363
Are you married?

13:52.365 --> 13:53.832
Kids?

13:53.834 --> 13:55.200
Still in New York?

13:55.202 --> 13:56.334
How is your Dad?

13:56.335 --> 13:57.467
All right, just one at a time.

13:58.405 --> 13:59.504
Are you married?

13:59.506 --> 14:00.905
No.

14:00.907 --> 14:01.940
Kids?

14:01.942 --> 14:03.474
No, how about you?

14:03.476 --> 14:05.343
Sorry, excuse me.

14:06.479 --> 14:07.579
Excuse me.

14:13.353 --> 14:15.954
So anyone working
here today or what?

14:15.956 --> 14:16.988
We are in Europe.

14:16.990 --> 14:19.490
That's true, this would
not happen in the States.

14:19.492 --> 14:21.492
Relax, it's not
such a bad thing.

14:25.932 --> 14:27.532
I miss your Dad, you know.

14:27.534 --> 14:29.868
He's so funny, I
really love him.

14:31.438 --> 14:33.037
Yeah.

14:33.039 --> 14:33.938
What's wrong?

14:37.377 --> 14:38.243
He died.

14:39.179 --> 14:40.078
What?

14:42.215 --> 14:43.114
Oh my God.

14:44.150 --> 14:44.983
How?

14:44.985 --> 14:46.517
When?

14:46.519 --> 14:47.552
It was like over a year ago now.

14:47.554 --> 14:48.987
And you didn't tell me?

14:48.989 --> 14:50.355
What happened?

14:50.357 --> 14:51.923
It was pancreatic cancer.

14:53.426 --> 14:55.460
They found it by
accident, actually.

14:55.462 --> 14:56.494
It was...

14:56.496 --> 14:58.263
Not good.

15:01.234 --> 15:02.533
I'm sorry.

15:02.535 --> 15:04.402
The doctors, couldn't
they do anything?

15:04.404 --> 15:05.570
It was too aggressive.

15:05.572 --> 15:07.539
They caught it too late.

15:07.540 --> 15:09.507
You know, he hated going to
doctors and stuff like that.

15:12.345 --> 15:13.678
I'm so sorry.

15:13.680 --> 15:14.579
Oh my God.

15:16.917 --> 15:18.416
I think about him often.

15:18.418 --> 15:20.418
Yeah.
I really do.

15:20.420 --> 15:22.120
He was such a lovely man.

15:23.256 --> 15:25.256
I mean, he was a crazy
son of a bitch though.

15:25.258 --> 15:26.291
You know that.

15:26.293 --> 15:27.425
Vincent.

15:27.427 --> 15:28.459
It's true like...

15:28.461 --> 15:31.362
Why is it that when
somebody dies everybody

15:31.364 --> 15:32.430
makes them out to
be saints, you know?

15:32.432 --> 15:33.965
It's bullshit.

15:33.967 --> 15:35.667
Just because someone's
dead we can't

15:35.669 --> 15:39.170
remember them for who they
really were, good and bad?

15:39.172 --> 15:40.571
He was fucking crazy.

15:40.573 --> 15:42.674
You know, he had the
fuse of a matchstick.

15:44.511 --> 15:46.044
He also had a heart of gold.

15:46.046 --> 15:47.612
I love him, I mean,
he was my Dad.

15:48.581 --> 15:50.448
There was a lot of
tough love there,

15:50.450 --> 15:54.552
but he would do anything for
the people that he cared about.

15:54.554 --> 15:55.453
That's true.

15:55.455 --> 15:58.690
He definitely marched to
the beat of his own drum.

15:58.692 --> 16:01.492
Didn't care what anybody
else thought about him.

16:01.494 --> 16:02.694
Everyone has to
go, he used to say.

16:02.696 --> 16:04.362
Don't act like you won't.

16:04.364 --> 16:05.196
Good advice.

16:05.198 --> 16:06.097
Yeah.

16:06.099 --> 16:09.600
Yeah, didn't really sink
in until he died though.

16:11.237 --> 16:13.338
I think it actually gave me
the strength to make a movie.

16:13.340 --> 16:15.407
Really?

16:15.408 --> 16:17.475
Yeah, I was terrified for
a long time, you know.

16:17.477 --> 16:19.094
What if people
don't like my work?

16:19.095 --> 16:20.712
What if I'm not as good
as I thought I was?

16:20.714 --> 16:23.448
What if my ambition
far exceeds my talent?

16:23.450 --> 16:24.515
Just all that stuff.

16:27.053 --> 16:29.554
I think it takes
real loss to realise

16:29.556 --> 16:32.156
that you don't have
anything to lose, you know?

16:34.561 --> 16:35.626
You miss him.

16:36.663 --> 16:37.562
Yeah.

16:40.567 --> 16:42.584
So anyway.

16:42.585 --> 16:44.602
What are you doing with
yourself these days?

16:44.604 --> 16:45.536
I'm in fashion.

16:47.340 --> 16:48.272
Big surprise.

16:48.274 --> 16:49.173
Hey!

16:50.043 --> 16:51.192
I'm just saying.

16:51.193 --> 16:52.342
We couldn't go passed a
single shop in New York

16:52.345 --> 16:54.078
without you dragging
me in there.

16:54.714 --> 16:59.183
You know, there was one time
I edited an entire short film

16:59.185 --> 17:01.486
on my laptop while I
was waiting for you.

17:01.488 --> 17:02.320
Bullshit.

17:02.322 --> 17:04.204
It's true.

17:04.205 --> 17:06.089
It was the mise-en-scene,
the one-shot film.

17:06.092 --> 17:08.343
We used to watch them in class.

17:08.344 --> 17:10.595
It was like the openings of
Orson Welles, Touch of Evil.

17:10.597 --> 17:12.230
P.T. Anderson, Boogie Nights.

17:12.232 --> 17:14.965
You remember all that?

17:14.967 --> 17:17.701
If it was one-shot then
what was there to edit?

17:17.704 --> 17:20.438
The titles and stuff, I mean.

17:20.440 --> 17:21.472
I don't know, I'm just saying.

17:21.473 --> 17:23.473
You spent a lot
of times in shops.

17:24.444 --> 17:26.111
Come on.

17:26.112 --> 17:27.779
Carrying all that
equipment, camera lights.

17:27.781 --> 17:30.048
And all the editing, too crazy.

17:30.050 --> 17:30.681
I like fashion.

17:30.683 --> 17:31.582
It's easy for me.

17:32.752 --> 17:34.752
That's 'cause you're
doing what you love.

17:34.754 --> 17:36.354
You know, if you're
doing what you love,

17:36.356 --> 17:38.222
there's no other
way to live, right?

17:38.224 --> 17:40.525
So you still love filmmaking?

17:40.527 --> 17:41.626
Mm.

17:41.628 --> 17:42.544
I don't know.

17:42.545 --> 17:43.461
I'll tell you after the Q&A.

17:43.463 --> 17:45.663
Come on, stop stressing.

17:47.300 --> 17:49.434
I'm just saying, film
school was never for you.

17:49.436 --> 17:51.369
Every time I looked at
you, you were drawing shoes

17:51.371 --> 17:52.603
or something like that.

17:54.541 --> 17:55.706
Don't tell me your making shoes?

17:55.708 --> 17:56.674
Designing.

17:56.676 --> 17:58.076
Designing shoes.

17:58.078 --> 17:59.644
For like the biggest
Italian labels.

17:59.646 --> 18:00.745
Oh, no shit?

18:00.747 --> 18:01.646
I'm serious!

18:03.416 --> 18:04.438
Wow.

18:04.439 --> 18:05.461
All that time waiting
around actually

18:05.462 --> 18:06.484
amounted to something, huh?

18:06.486 --> 18:08.419
Hm, very funny.

18:08.421 --> 18:10.555
I might not be telling
stories like you,

18:10.557 --> 18:13.124
but when I see women wearing
shoes that I designed,

18:13.126 --> 18:15.093
and they look strong,
